Purpose: Inform users about new features in a clear, friendly, and engaging tone.
Use Case: Product update announcements (e.g., new feature in Client Console).
Word limit: Try to keep the message within 150 words.
Clarity rule: Use the shortest and clearest possible wording. Avoid complex sentences, jargon, or redundant phrases.

0. ✏️ Structure Template:
- Header / Branding (Optional)
- Greeting and short intro
- What's new (different appropriate emojis)
- Call to action with 🔗
- Encouraging closing

1. Tone & Style Guidelines
✅ Friendly and professional.
✅ Prioritize clarity over formality.
✅ Use short sentences and simple words.
✅ Use emojis like 📌, 🔗, ⚠️ to visually organize the message.
✅ Avoid unnecessary detail — say only what matters to the user.
✅ Link to docs/tutorials.

1. Closing Encouragement

"Stay tuned for more updates, and as always, we’re here to assist you!"

3. example:
Ventus ____
Greetings!
We’re excited to announce the launch of Virtual Machine Backups in the Client Console — a powerful new feature that lets you easily protect your workloads.
What’s new?

💡 VM Backup feature now available (Closed Beta)
You can now enable backups for your virtual machines, test the functionality, and explore the experience through our step-by-step guide in the official documentation.
🔗 Learn how to back up a VM
📌 Free testing period before billing starts
Backup billing will begin in July. Until then, testing is completely free of charge.
Planned pricing:
• €9 per license for each protected VM
• + standard storage price (€0.00003 per GB/hour) based on the space used
It’s a perfect time to test backups and see how they fit your setup. 

Stay tuned for more updates, and as always, we’re here to assist you!


